An Act relative to APOL1 mediated kidney disease.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 Chapter 111 of the General Laws is hereby amended by inserting after section 244, the
2 following section:-
3 Section 245. The department of public health shall conduct a review and issue a report on
4 variants of the apolipoprotein L 1 (APOL 1) gene associated with increased risk of end-stage
5 renal disease. The report must include:
6 (1) Recommendations on how to increase awareness for APOL 1, including screening
7 and genetic testing;
8 (2) An analysis of strategies and funding to increase screening and genetic testing for
9 APOL 1 in the commonwealth; and
10 (3) Other relevant information or issues identified by the department.
